ical thinking of Paul Cohen. The translation includes Susan Spitzer's extensive notes clarifying allusions and "ations and hinting at Badiou's intentions. An interview with Badiou encompasses the play's settings, themes, and events, as well as his ongoing literary and conceptual experimentation on stage and off.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aFrench literaturey21st century. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Deconstruction.2bisacsh1 aReinhard, Kenneth.1 aSpitzer, Susan.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066254208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044247208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311045952440uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/badi15774423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231527736.jpg  a978-3-11-044247-2  CUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013  a978-3-11-045952-4  CUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066254-2  CUP eBook Package 2000-2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG